The paper deals with distributed estimation in a network of agents, which involves communication and sensing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Machine Learning (cs.MA), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Learning (cs.LG). Among these, cs.IT and cs.SY are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the problem of distributed estimation and control. The use of linear combinations and additive Gaussian noise also suggests a connection to signal processing and communications, which are sub-fields of cs.IT and cs.SY. The use of algorithms and simulations also suggests a connection to cs.MA and cs.LG, while the focus on dynamic networks suggests a connection to cs.NI.
